ENTRY            30143   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30143001   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 15         41
TITLE      Fission spectrum averaged cross sections of threshold
            reactions
AUTHOR     (J.W.Boldeman)
INSTITUTE  (3AULAUA)
REFERENCE  (J,JNE/AB,18,417,1964)
FACILITY   (REAC,3AULAUA) MOATA reactor
INC-SOURCE (REAC) Moata reactor of UTR10 type with neutron
           converter, see 'INC-SPEC'.
           .Samples were irradiated at center of a neutron
            converter consisting of an air-cooled hollow cylinder
            of enriched U-Al alloy,2.5 cm dia.,10 cm long,
            containing 10 gram of U-235.
INC-SPECT  Spectrum at the center of neutron converter conformed
            closely to the U-235 fission spectrum. Fast flux was
            4.14 X 10**10 n/cm2/sec. Daily variation was monitored
            27Al(n,alpha)24Na reaction. Fast flux from fuel
            elements was 10**9 n/cm2/sec, less than 2.5% of fast
            flux inside the converter.
SAMPLE     Spectrographically pure metals or oxides.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) The absolute activity of the samples were
            measured using NaI(Tl) crystal spectrometers of
            various sizes (1 X 14 inches, 8 X 4 inches; and
            2 X 2 inches crystals in 4pi geometry)
           (PROPC) 4pi beta- proportional counter was used for
            counting the separated beta-emitting products of
            31P(n,p)31Si and 32S(n,p)32P
MONITOR    (16-S-32(N,P)15-P-32,,SIG,,FIS)
MONIT-REF  (30143016,J.W.BOLDEMAN,J,JNE/AB,18,417,1964)
METHOD     (ACTIV)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,J.W.Boldeman,J,JNE/AB,18,417,1964) Table 3
